+# Exotic Knob
+
+Exotic Knob is a local baseline CLI for learning what an Anticater VK-01 Bluetooth
+volume knob emits before building daemon behavior or NAD M33 BluOS volume control.
+
+## Quick start
+
+```bash
+python -m pip install -e ".[dev]"
+python -m exotic_knob.cli.main --help
+python -m exotic_knob.cli.main replay --fixture tests/fixtures/anticater/sample_reports.jsonl
+```
+
+Real HID capture is optional and needs HIDAPI:
+
+```bash
+brew install hidapi
+python -m pip install -e ".[dev,hid]"
+python -m exotic_knob.cli.main list
+python -m exotic_knob.cli.main capture --path "<device-path>" --output capture.local.jsonl --limit 20
+```
+
+Pair the knob through the operating system first. The CLI does not perform
+Bluetooth pairing, does not control LEDs/RGB, and does not send amplifier volume
+commands in this baseline.
+
+## Checks
+
+```bash
+just test
+just lint
+just smoke
+```
+
+If `just` is unavailable, run the commands from `justfile` directly.
+
+Captured fixtures may contain local HID paths or serial numbers. Redact local
+identity fields before sharing fixtures publicly.
+
